			h5 APPLICATION FOR VARIABLE VAV TERMINAL FANS  
			p
				|VAV systems were developed in response to the early 1970's energy crisis. 
				|These systems reduced energy usage, sometimes at the expense of comfort. 
				|But today's building owners want the VAV system's economy without sacrificing comfort.
			p
				|Many applications require a VAV terminal fan to achieve satisfactory comfort.
				| Recent advances in air moving motor technology allow efficient variable speed operation of these fans.
			p
				|Variable speed fans may be applied to improve comfort and save energy.
